    "However, to overcome the heterogeneity present in the data, we conducted some independent analyses for several groups.",
    "As such, all statistical results should be interpreted with extreme caution.",
    "Nonetheless, small sample sizes are found very often in studies dealing with patients with brain tumors [1] [2] [3] [4] [5] 41 possibly due to current standardized protocols disregarding pre-surgery functional acquisitions, rather simple diffusion sequences and the lack of multi-site initiatives [60] [61] [62].",
